A guest holds the invitation card depicting a black and white portrait of late French designer Thierry Mugler at the protestant church of the Oratory of the Louvre in Paris on February 4, 2022, prior to his funeral service after he died at 73 of "natural causes" on January 23, 2022. AFP/STEPHANE DE SAKUTIN PARIS - Mourners have gathered to pay their respects to famed fashion designer Thierry Mugler at a funeral service held in Paris. Mugler died last month aged 73. His funeral was attended by prominent figures in the fashion industry, actors, and politicians. He dressed countless celebrities around the globe including Diana Ross, Madonna, Beyoncé, and Kim Kardashian. Mugler was born in Strasbourg, France, he moved to Paris when he was 24 and opened his first boutique in 1978.